race.comment: THINKING GOLD (7) resumed over a mile in good order narrowly beaten at Pakenham. Proven second-up and has more to offer. The extra metres will suit him on his way to longer trips. Maps for a soft run and Nolen sticks aboard the Moody-Coleman-trained galloper. VIVACISSIMO (8) is also in good hands and is a threat. Peaks off three placed efforts and is back a touch in grade off the latest. The 3kg claim brings her right into it. BLUE COWBOY (3) led and was too good for the 62 graders at Geelong over this distance. He's heading in the right direction and gets in well with the 3kg claim. Will skip across and is a candidate to lead. BROOKLYN BOSS (5) will find this more suitable than The Heath, and fitter again is in the mix. QUITE THE LASS (11) also presents third-up and should be around the mark.
